# Target URLs for WAF Testing
# One URL per line. Lines starting with # are comments.
# Supports full URLs with paths, endpoints, and query parameters

# Example: Test root domain
https://example.com

# Example: Test specific endpoints
https://example.com/api/search
https://example.com/api/users
https://example.com/login
https://example.com/admin/dashboard

# Example: Test with existing query parameters
https://api.example.com/v1/products?category=electronics
https://api.example.com/v2/search?q=test

# Example: Multiple domains
https://app1.example.com
https://app2.example.com
https://staging.example.com

# Example: Different ports
https://example.com:8443/api
http://example.com:8080/test

# Example: Subdomains
https://api.example.com/v1/endpoint
https://admin.example.com/panel
https://blog.example.com/search
